\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## \uc0\u55356 \u57283  Running Locally
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### Prerequisites
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf0 \strokec4  Python 3.11+\cb1 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf0 \strokec4  [\cf6 \strokec6 Ollama\cf0 \strokec4 ](\ul https://ollama.com\ulnone ) installed\cb1 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf0 \strokec4  Groq API key (free at [\cf6 \strokec6 console.groq.com\cf0 \strokec4 ](\ul https://console.groq.com\ulnone ))\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ### Steps
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 **1. Clone the repository**
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3 git \cf6 \strokec6 clone\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 https://github.com/srj17-max/mining-law-ai.git\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 cd \cf6 \strokec6 mining-law-ai\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 **2. Create a virtual environment**
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3 python \cf6 \strokec6 -m\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 venv\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 venv\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 source \cf6 \strokec6 venv/bin/activate\cf0 \strokec4         \cf9 \strokec9 # Mac/Linux\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 venv\\Scripts\\activate           \cf9 \strokec9 # Windows\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 **3. Install dependencies**
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3 pip \cf6 \strokec6 install\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 -r\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 requirements.txt\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 **4. Add your Groq API key**
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3 mkdir \cf6 \strokec6 -p\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 .streamlit\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 nano \cf6 \strokec6 .streamlit/secrets.toml\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\cb3 Add this inside:\cb1 \
\cb3 ```toml\cb1 \
\cb3 GROQ_API_KEY = "your_groq_api_key_here"\cb1 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 **5. Run the app**
\f1\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3 streamlit \cf6 \strokec6 run\cf0 \strokec4  \cf6 \strokec6 app_ui.py\cf0 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
\
\cb3 The app will open at \cf2 \strokec2 `http://localhost:8501`\cf0 \strokec4 . On first run it will build the FAISS index from the PDFs (takes 2\'965 minutes). Subsequent runs load instantly.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

